<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in the face of something • on the face of something </xh5><p> <i>in the face of something—</i>in the presence of smth.; when confronted with smth.: He can’t possibly win <u>in the face of</u> such difficulties.</p><p><i>on the face of something—</i>from appearances of smth.; judging from smth.: <u>On the face of</u> the results, the examination was too difficult.</p> </entry>
